    pm-8fvl,related,"2026-03-05T11:05:52.887Z",cursor-maintainer,null
  comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
    "2026-03-05T11:05:52.887Z",cursor-maintainer,"Gap verified by probe command: pnpm dlx pm-cli@latest --json test-all currently bypasses recursion guard."
    "2026-03-05T11:06:13.568Z",cursor-maintainer,"Planned changeset: update PRD/README/AGENTS to explicitly include pnpm dlx and npm exec package launcher recursion forms, then harden src/cli/commands/test.ts parsing and extend unit regressions for add-time rejection plus runtime skip parity."
    "2026-03-05T11:07:05.887Z",cursor-maintainer,"Docs-first alignment completed: updated PRD README and AGENTS recursive test-all safety wording to explicitly include pnpm dlx and npm exec package launcher forms alongside existing pm and npx examples."
    "2026-03-05T11:20:20.643Z",cursor-maintainer,"Implemented launcher-parser hardening in src/cli/commands/test.ts: recursive test-all detection now evaluates pnpm dlx and npm exec/x package-launcher forms in addition to existing pm/node/npx handling, while preserving token-aware flag and env parsing semantics."
    "2026-03-05T11:20:20.789Z",cursor-maintainer,"Evidence: pm test pm-11t5 --run --timeout 2400 --json passed (linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0) with coverage report at 100% lines/branches/functions/statements; pm test-all --status in_progress --timeout 2400 --json passed (items=1 linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0 skipped=0); pm test-all --status closed --timeout 2400 --json passed (items=68 linked_tests=212 passed=59 failed=0 skipped=153)."
    "2026-03-05T11:30:11.746Z",cursor-maintainer,"Post-refactor verification (latest code): pm test pm-11t5 --run --timeout 2400 --json passed with linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0 and 100% coverage across lines/branches/functions/statements; pm test-all --status in_progress --timeout 2400 --json passed (items=1 linked_tests=2 passed=2 failed=0 skipped=0); pm test-all --status closed --timeout 2400 --json passed (items=68 linked_tests=212 passed=59 failed=0 skipped=153)."
